frameDefinitions: An Agent (the punisher or rewarder) performs a Response_action on an Evaluee for a Reason, the Evaluee's actions or beliefs.
A Cognizer carries out an approximate calculation or considers some Evidence so as to arrive at an approximate Value for some Feature of an Item.
A Cognizer makes a judgment about an Evaluee.
A Competition comes to an end, with a Competitor tying, winning, or losing against an Opponent (or opponents) according to their Score.
A Communicator communicates a judgment of an Evaluee to an Addressee.
An Assessor examines a Phenomenon to figure out its Value according to some Feature of the Phenomenon.
frameExamples: His <t>punishment</t> of the prisoners was too harsh.
Until 1971, dolphin mortality could be <t>estimated</t> only from analyses of vessels ' logbooks -- and the figures are probably underestimates. CNI
JUDGMENT:  She <t>admired</t> Einstein for his character.
